ith a vast array of objects ranging from the classics of the cinephile canon to television news programs, home movies and mobile phone films.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aLinguistics. 4aMedia Studies. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aCommunication, pragmatics, media, arts, cinema.1 aHediger, Vinzenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarbach, Ségolène.1 aOdin, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048538669?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048538669zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048538669/original  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA